result.execSummary:
The defendant Doris Cordero was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

ADA Melissa Inlow appears for the State.  Defendant appeared in person and with Attorney Poss.  Defendant plead no contest to Count 1.  Court reviewed plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant.  Defendant understood.  Defense stipulated to factual basis.  Court found that the defendant freely voluntarily and intelligently entered her plea, and waived her constitutional rights.  Factual basis exists.  Found guilty as plead to.   ADA recommended  $100 fine, plus costs.  Attorney Poss agrees and this is a joint recommendation.  Defendant elected to not exercise her right to allocution.  Court ordered $100.00, plus costs.  Pay @ $100 per month, starting 5/1.    Failure to pay any part of the fine or court costs in full by the due date will result in 1 day jail for each $25 left unpaid.
